MONGO DATABASE COMMANDS:
------------------------


TO ENTER THE MONGO CONSOLE:
1.
	> mongo
	> mongo your_database_name
	> mongo --host your_host --port your_port
	> mongo -u your_username -p your_password --authenticationDatabase your_auth_database


TO SHOW DBS:
1. show Databases

TO BACKUP:
1.
	> mongodump --db=mydatabase --out=/path/to/backup/directory
	> mongodump --db=mydatabase --host=your_host --port=your_port --out=/path/to/backup/directory
	> mongodump --db=mydatabase -u your_username -p your_password --authenticationDatabase your_auth_database --out=/path/to/backup/directory

TO RESTORE:
1.
	> mongorestore --db=mydatabase /path/to/backup/directory/mydatabase
	> mongorestore --db=mydatabase --host=your_host --port=your_port /path/to/backup/directory/mydatabase
	> mongorestore --db=mydatabase -u your_username -p your_password --authenticationDatabase your_auth_database /path/to/backup/directory/mydatabase

TO CREATE:
1. mongo
2. use DBname

TO DROP:
1. mongo 
2. use mydatabase
3. db.dropDatabase()

